21:52.879 --> 21:54.523
John, we will be able
to give you a room,

21:54.547 --> 21:57.125
although here we
call them cells.

21:57.149 --> 22:00.887
Erm, from the Latin cellar,
sort of a small room where a,

22:04.123 --> 22:05.443
like where a nun
or a monk sleeps.

22:07.794 --> 22:09.634
We'll take it from there,
does that sound okay?

22:11.531 --> 22:12.531
Yeah.

22:13.766 --> 22:15.678
So how will you treat him?

22:15.702 --> 22:17.742
We'll give him what he wants,
we'll give him a cell.

22:19.706 --> 22:22.675
And if he wants to
talk, we'll listen.

22:25.144 --> 22:26.555
And that's it?

22:26.579 --> 22:27.579
Yeah.

22:39.592 --> 22:40.592
Come on.

22:55.742 --> 22:57.510
Mama was struggling.

22:58.878 --> 23:01.957
She held onto him, kept
saying please don't,

23:01.981 --> 23:04.717
please don't please,
please don't.

23:09.789 --> 23:12.091
I was just a little
boy of seven.

23:14.627 --> 23:15.627
I saw it all.

23:17.930 --> 23:18.930
I,

23:21.868 --> 23:24.604
I can't get rid of
the smell of...

23:31.143 --> 23:35.791
Sydney, I'll try and
help you let go of this.

23:35.815 --> 23:38.417
I can't promise it will be easy.

23:39.819 --> 23:41.053
Thank you.

